      "body" : "Packages hep.aida.* are LGPL (<a href=\"http://acs.lbl.gov/software/colt/license.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">acs.lbl.gov/software/colt/license.html</a>). This is imported via colt (<a href=\"http://jung.sourceforge.net/download.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">jung.sourceforge.net/download.html</a>). This prevents JUNG from being used in projects under the umbrella of ASF and ESF. Maybe one should use the github fork <a href=\"https://github.com/rortian/jung2\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">github.com/rortian/jung2</a> and remove that dependency. <a href=\"https://github.com/rortian/jung2/commit/f4ca0cdcd3312589cbb48de7350b84cbff6067b9\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">github.com/rortian/jung2/commit/&hellip;</a> is mirroring the last CVS commit. The current commits seem to remove visualization functionality."
